In pictures: global protests over Egypt
Around 100 residents of the Syrian capital Damascus showed their solidarity with Egyptian protesters by holding a candlelight vigil.
In London students demonstrating against tuition fees also joined the crowds outside the Egyptian embassy to show their support.
Hundreds of people demonstrated in front of the White House in Washington DC to show their anger with President Mubarak and to urge the US administration to "stand on the right side of history".
Young protesters in Atlanta, Georgia showing their support for Egypt's pro-democracy movement. There were demonstrations in many other US cities including New York, Chicago and San Francisco.
Egyptian immigrants living in Athens made their feelings known outside their embassy.
Hundreds of people gathered in front of the Egyptian embassy in Beirut, including this child standing in front of a protest banner.